@Jackie-Jiang I don't understand how do you propose to make the message more crisp. How do you know, in pinot-`MultiStageBrokerRequestHandler` (or `QueryEnvironment`) the actual error reason? The only way I think we have is to parse the message of the exception (looking for something that starts with `Failed to find enabled fully replicated server for table:`), which seems like a very bad idea. Is there something I'm missing?

Remember that we don't just want to change the error message, we also want to provide a more specific error code. In my example we return 715 instead of the generic 150.

Do you propose to include the exception trace or not?
